docs.abstract: A movement spearheaded by a black creative director in Brooklyn is urging major retailers to commit to devoting a set amount of their shelf space to black-owned businesses.
docs.snippet: A movement spearheaded by a black creative director in Brooklyn is urging major retailers to commit to devoting a set amount of their shelf space to black-owned businesses.
docs.lead_paragraph: As protests over police brutality swept the country in recent weeks and major retailers posted messages of solidarity with black Americans on social media, Aurora James, a creative director in Brooklyn, asked herself if she actually felt that those brands were standing with her as a black woman and business owner.

headline.main: Sephora Signs ‘15 Percent Pledge’ to Carry More Black-Owned Brands
headline.print_headline: ‘15 Percent Pledge’: Sephora Signs a Vow To Push Black Brands

docs.abstract: In a Fox News interview, President Trump was vague in his answer on a key issue in police reform efforts.
docs.snippet: In a Fox News interview, President Trump was vague in his answer on a key issue in police reform efforts.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump appeared to support outlawing chokeholds as a law enforcement practice in an interview with Fox News that aired on Friday, but not before he defended their use in certain situations in a rambling response to a question about police reform efforts.

headline.main: Trump Says He Opposes Police Chokeholds, Except in Certain Situations
headline.print_headline: Trump Says He Opposes Police Chokeholds, Maybe

docs.abstract: Those who knew Jackson during his 14-year N.B.A. career are not surprised at how he has worked tirelessly as an activist in support of his friend George Floyd.
docs.snippet: Those who knew Jackson during his 14-year N.B.A. career are not surprised at how he has worked tirelessly as an activist in support of his friend George Floyd.
docs.lead_paragraph: Just a few months after being jettisoned by the Indiana Pacers and joining the Golden State Warriors in 2007, Stephen Jackson helped his new team upset the 67-win Dallas Mavericks in the opening round of the N.B.A. playoffs. By the beginning of the following season, Jackson had picked up a new nickname to paste over the old troublemaker label that led Indiana to trade him.

headline.main: Stephen Jackson Was Known in the N.B.A. as an Agitator. Now He’s Leading a Movement.
headline.print_headline: A Stalwart Leader  Follows His Heart

docs.abstract: This time is different. Here’s why.
docs.snippet: This time is different. Here’s why.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the wake of a perverse constellation of deaths of black Americans at the hands of the police and vigilantes, America’s current incarnation of a civil rights movement —  organized under the rallying cry of “Black Lives Matter” — is more powerful than ever.

docs.abstract: What started as a renewed push for police reform has now touched seemingly every aspect of American life.
docs.snippet: What started as a renewed push for police reform has now touched seemingly every aspect of American life.
docs.lead_paragraph: The reckonings have been swift and dizzying.

headline.main: From Cosmetics to NASCAR, Calls for Racial Justice Are Spreading
headline.print_headline: An Awakening in America Is Prying at Racism’s Grip

docs.abstract: The Off-White and Louis Vuitton designer has become a target of social media anger and frustration because of statements about the protests.
docs.snippet: The Off-White and Louis Vuitton designer has become a target of social media anger and frustration because of statements about the protests.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 2018, when Louis Vuitton named Virgil Abloh as its men’s wear artistic director, it made Mr. Abloh, the founder of Off-White, a Nike collaborator and the former creative director for Kanye West, one of the first black designers at the top of a French heritage house.

headline.print_headline: Remarks About Protesters Disappoint a Designer’s Fans

docs.abstract: The city received 1,737 fireworks complaints in the first half of June, 80 times as many as it got in the same period last year.
docs.snippet: The city received 1,737 fireworks complaints in the first half of June, 80 times as many as it got in the same period last year.
docs.lead_paragraph: New York, an already-jittery city transformed by the coronavirus pandemic and protests against police brutality and systemic racism, now has its own cacophonous soundtrack: illegal fireworks being set off in soaring numbers from late afternoon until the wee hours of the morning.

headline.main: New Woe for a Jittery N.Y.C.: Illegal Fireworks Going Off All Night
headline.print_headline: Fireworks, and Tempers, Are Blowing Up at Night

byline.original: By Corey Kilgannon and Juliana Kim
